"(T) As I put the twins in cryo, I could not contain my tears. I knew this was goodbye, but even in that moment they were still trying to cheer me up. They trusted me, and I was betraying their trust. I was sending them, all alone and helpless, to an unfamiliar and inhospitable place.

They will adapt and survive, without a shadow of a doubt, but will they be able to understand and forgive me?

Because right now, I can't even forgive myself. ^cyan;>>^reset;",

"(T) We spent the previous night around a small campfire. They never liked fires, but seemed to feel safer while I was around. It was a good evening, filled with many positive emotions; but my knowing that it was to be our last made my every smile feel insincere.

